Capitals Beat Rangers, Canucks Overcome Blackhawks in NHL Playoff Openers

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-14T05:44:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/capitals-beat-rangers-canucks-defeat-blackhawks-in-nhl-playoff-openers.html
The top-seeded  Washington  Capitals
beat the  New York Rangers  in overtime to take a 1-0 lead in the
National Hockey League Eastern Conference quarterfinals.  Alexander Semin scored with 96 seconds left in the first
overtime last night at the Verizon Center to give the Capitals
 a 2-1 win over the eighth-seeded Rangers. Game 2 in the 
best-of-seven series is tomorrow in Washington.  After two scoreless periods, Matt Gilroy got a goal less
than two minutes into the third period to give the Rangers a 1-0
lead. Twelve minutes later,  Alex Ovechkin  tied the game.  At Rogers Arena in Vancouver, the top-seeded Vancouver
Canucks defeated the defending Stanley Cup champion  Chicago 
Blackhawks 2-0 to open their Western Conference quarterfinal.  Chris Higgins and Jannik Hansen each scored in the first
period against the eighth-seeded Blackhawks. The Canucks host
Game 2 tomorrow before the best-of-seven series switches to
Chicago for two matches.  In other opening games last night, it was Detroit 4,
Phoenix 2; Pittsburgh 3, Tampa Bay 0; and Nashville 4, Anaheim
1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
